1-Minute Version (High Impact + Concise)
[SPEAKER 1] — Opening
Welcome everyone. Corporates worldwide are making bold climate commitments — net zero, carbon neutrality, sustainable growth. But the biggest challenge today is not ambition. It is execution. And that is the gap we are here to solve.
[SPEAKER 2] — The Problem
95% of HSBC’s corporate clients see sustainability as a competitive advantage, yet most struggle to implement it. Why? Fragmented emissions data, unmanaged Scope 3 supply chains, complex global regulations, and limited access to timely green financing. The result — companies know they must transition, but they don’t know how.
[SPEAKER 3] — Why It Matters
And the impact is even greater on SMEs — the backbone of global supply chains. They lack the resources, expertise, and funding to navigate sustainability alone. The ecosystem needs a single platform that can guide every stakeholder together.
[HARSHADA] — The Solution
That is exactly what we built — the HSBC Sustainable Transition Copilot. An AI-powered sustainability ecosystem that connects operational data, maps carbon emissions across all three scopes, and delivers a funded transition roadmap with AI recommendations, green vendors, subsidies, and HSBC financing in one place. Corporates gain resilience and cost savings, suppliers get a clear path forward, and HSBC becomes not just the bank behind the transition — but the operating system powering it.
